    <!-- Origin -->
    <h2>Origin</h2>
    <p>"Lighthouse" was the name of the house Bob lived in during college, where he first began studying finance and economics. What started as a nickname stuck, and over the years it evolved into the identity of the firm: a signal through the noise, a fixed point of reference in volatile markets. That's how Lighthouse Macro was born, and where "Macro, Illuminated" comes from.</p>
    <p>Bob's neurodivergent wiring is core to the firm's edge. Where most analysts specialize in one domain and stay there, his ADHD-driven intellectual restlessness pushes him across the full macro landscape: Fed plumbing, labor economics, credit markets, Treasury microstructure, crypto integration, technical analysis, and quantitative modeling. The result isn't breadth without depth. It's institutional-grade expertise across multiple domains, and the ability to see connections specialists miss by staying in silos. The 12-pillar framework exists because Bob's mind naturally operates across all 12 simultaneously.</p>

    <!-- Core Philosophy -->
    <h2>Investment Philosophy</h2>
    <p>We hold <span class="emphasis">strong opinions, weakly held</span>. Every position carries maximum conviction at entry, backed by a systematic framework and clear data. But conviction without discipline is just stubbornness. Every thesis comes with explicit invalidation criteria: the specific data points that would prove us wrong.</p>
    <p>When invalidation triggers fire, we act. No anchoring. No narrative defense. The framework drives positioning, but the framework can be wrong. Data determines outcome.</p>

    <div class="philosophy-grid">
        <div class="phil-card">
            <h3>Conviction-Weighted</h3>
            <p>3-10 high-conviction positions sized by framework score. We concentrate where the edge is clearest rather than diversifying the signal away across 30+ marginal positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phil-card">
            <h3>Clear Invalidations</h3>
            <p>Every thesis has an exit door. Bull case, bear case, specific thresholds. If the data says we're wrong, we rotate. No ego in the portfolio.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phil-card">
            <h3>Flows Over Stocks</h3>
            <p>We track what's happening at the margin, not the cumulative result. Labor flows, Fed plumbing dynamics, credit conditions. The leading signals, not the lagging headlines.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phil-card">
            <h3>Cash as a Position</h3>
            <p>30-100% cash is a valid allocation. When the framework signals elevated risk and structure breaks down, the best trade is no trade. Cash is not a residual, it is an active choice.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Framework -->
    <h2>The Diagnostic Dozen</h2>
    <p>Twelve macro pillars organized into three engines. Each pillar generates a proprietary composite index. Together they feed the <span class="emphasis">Macro Risk Index (MRI)</span>, our master regime indicator that synthesizes the full macro landscape into a single actionable signal.</p>

    <div class="engines">
        <div class="engine">
            <h3>Macro Dynamics</h3>
            <div class="pills">Pillars 1-7</div>
            <p>Labor, Prices, Growth, Housing, Consumer, Business, Trade</p>
        </div>
        <div class="engine">
            <h3>Monetary Mechanics</h3>
            <div class="pills">Pillars 8-10</div>
            <p>Government, Financial Conditions, Fed Plumbing</p>
        </div>
        <div class="engine">
            <h3>Market Structure</h3>
            <div class="pills">Pillars 11-12</div>
            <p>Breadth, Momentum, Sentiment, Positioning</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="convergence">&#x2193; All 12 pillars converge into the Macro Risk Index (MRI) &#x2193;</div>
    <p>When all three engines confirm, conviction is maximum. When they diverge, exposure is reduced. The convergence requirement prevents single-factor mistakes.</p>

